&lt;h3&gt;Pesach 6 (Chol Hamoed)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add Ya&#039;aleh v&#039;Yavo for Pesach to the Amidah (MT 92)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite Half Hallel after the Amidah (MT 560).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading - Traditional&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numbers 9:1-14 (P 1081, RP 954, WTC 848)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;4 Aliyot&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading - Alternative&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numbers 9:1-5 (P 1081, RP 954, WTC 848)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OR&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deuteronomy 16:13-17 (P 1450, RP 1274, WTC 1133)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Shacharit Torah Reading Scroll #2&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Numbers 28:19-25 (P 1211, RP 1083, WTC 978)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Aliyah&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Mincha&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add Ya&#039;aleh v&#039; Yavo for Pesach to the Amidah (MT 92)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Candlelighting&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before dark, we light candles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We say the festival and Shabbat candle blessing (MT 384) but not shehecheyanu.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Ma&#039;ariv&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival Amidah with appropriate additions for Pesach (MT 470)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Count the omer before Aleinu (MT 570).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Include appropriate additions for Shabbat as indicated in the Siddur.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;During Dinner&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite the festival evening Kiddush (MT 286)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add Ya&#039;aleh v&#039;Yavo for Pesach and Harachaman for Yom Tov to Birkat Hamazon. Also include R&#039;tzei and Harachaman for Shabbat.&lt;/p&gt;
